# Generated configs (orchestrator-written at runtime).
#
# These paths must match `app/sessions_orchestrator.py`:
#   COMPOSE_FRAGMENT = Path("/data/generated/docker-compose.sessions.yml")
#   NGINX_FRAGMENT   = Path("/data/generated/nginx-sessions.conf")
# which inside the web/worker containers map to host paths via the bind
# mount `./generated:/data/generated` in docker-compose.yml.
#
# Audit-2026-05 #29 — pre-this-fix the patterns below were
# `docker/docker-compose.sessions.yml` and `docker/nginx/sessions.conf`,
# which never matched anything. The operator-modified runtime state
# leaked into `git status` and caused stash/pop dances during deploys.
#
# Audit-2026-05 #30 — these files are now fully untracked (git rm --cached'd
# in v0.1.32.10). On a fresh clone, `bin/viator-bootstrap-stubs.sh` writes
# empty stubs so compose's parse-time `include:` succeeds; the web
# container's _startup hook then regenerates them from current DB state.
# These patterns are kept as belt-and-braces — the files should never come
# back to the index even if someone forgets and runs `git add -A`.
docker/generated/docker-compose.sessions.yml
docker/generated/nginx-sessions.conf

# Pure runtime files — never tracked.
docker/generated/.reload-trigger
inbox-staging/

# OneDrive cruft (in case the repo lives in a OneDrive folder)
*.lnk
